Ruby programmer? It’s easy to use this data in your own app! Use the gem like this: 

require 'everypolitician'
country = Everypolitician::Index.new.country('Germany')
house = country.legislature('Bundestag')
house.popolo.terms.find_by(id: 'term/5').memberships.each do |membership|
  puts "#{membership.person.name} (#{membership.party.name}): #{membership.person.gender}"
end

Libraries also available in Python and PHP.

Main Sources: https://de.wikipedia.org/wiki/Liste_der_Listen_der_Mitglieder_des_Deutschen_Bundestages, http://wikidata.org/
